Lunaris Privacy Policy
Effective Date: April 3, 2026 Last Updated: April 3, 2026

At Lunaris Development, we are committed to being transparent about the data we collect and how it is used to provide our services. This policy outlines our data practices for the Lunaris Discord bot and associated services.

1. Information We Collect
We only collect data that is necessary for the bot's functionality and to improve your experience.

A. Discord Metadata
Identifiers: We process your Discord User ID, Server (Guild) ID, and Channel IDs to identify you and your server.
Profile Information: We may access your Discord tag and avatar URL for display on profile cards and logs.
B. Usage & Engagement Metrics
Activity Stats: We track cumulative counts of messages sent, time spent in voice channels, and total commands executed.
Rolling Activity: We maintain a rolling 30-day log of your daily message, voice, and command activity to provide "last 30 days" statistics.
XP & Leveling: We calculate and store Experience Points (XP) and Levels based on your engagement.
C. Music & Playlists
Listening History: We store a history of your last 30 played tracks (title, author, and URL).
Custom Playlists: We store playlists you create within the bot.
D. Settings & Personalization
Preferences: Custom bot prefixes, accent colors, and 24/7 mode settings for your server.
Greetings: Personalized join/leave messages, including custom text and audio links if configured.
E. Moderation & Support
Moderation Records: We maintain logs of warnings and mutes (including reasons, durations, and moderator IDs).
Tickets & Reminders: Data associated with support tickets and active reminders you set.
Feedback & Reports: Any information you provide via the /feedback, /suggest, or /report commands is sent to our development team for review.
F. Premium Services
Subscription Data: We track your premium tier, granting administrator, and expiration date.
2. How We Use Your Data
We use the collected information for the following purposes:

Core Functionality: To play music, manage server moderation, and maintain your settings.
Experience Gamification: To provide leveling, XP, and profile display features.
Service Improvement: To analyze feedback and bug reports to enhance bot performance.
Premium Management: To verify and provide access to premium features.
3. Data Retention & Security
Retention: Most statistical data (XP, total counts) is kept while the bot is in your server. Activity logs are on a rolling 30-day cycle. You can request data deletion at any time.
Security: Your data is stored in secure databases. Access is strictly limited to authorized development team members for maintenance and support purposes.
No Selling: We NEVER sell, rent, or trade your personal data with third parties.
4. Your Rights
Under the GDPR and other privacy frameworks, you have the right to:

Access: Request to see what data we have stored about you.
Deletion: Request the permanent removal of your data from our systems.
Opt-out: You may opt-out by removing the bot from your server or discontinuing its use.
To exercise your rights or ask questions, please contact us via our Support Server.

By using Lunaris, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
